However, 80% of them require ventilator support, and this is much more common than in COVID-19 patients, which is almost the same as MERS, which poses a higher threat to life than COVID-19.
Diarrhea (26%) and sore throat (21%) were also observed in MERS patients.
Fever (99% to 100%), wheezing (29% to 75%), shortness of breath (40% to 42%), diarrhoea (20% to 25%) and sore throat (13%) are the main symptoms in SARS patients, and respiratory support is required in almost 14% to 20% of patients.
