Mass transmission is usually within the same family, or from a common gathering of friends, or from a vehicle such as a luxury cruise ship.
The patients are those who have a travel history within two weeks prior to the onset of symptoms or who have been in contact with residents of Wuhan or other areas where the infection is present or infected or with patients.
