When handling surfaces or bodily fluids that may be contaminated, or when servicing a sick passenger, flight attendants should wear disposable medical gloves. If possible, flight attendants should wear additional personal protective equipment if they detect signs of fever or persistent coughing or breathing difficulties in a sick passenger.
